==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''coconut''' (''plural:'' '''[[coconuts]]''')

# the [[fruit]] of the [[coco palm]], ''[[Cocos nucifera]]'', having a [[fibrous]] [[husk]] surrounding a large [[seed]]
# the hard-shelled seed of this fruit, having white flesh and a [[fluid]]-filled central [[cavity]]
# the [[edible]] white flesh of this fruit
# the coconut [[palm]]
# (''person'') a mildly pejorative slang term used to describe people who are "brown" (Hispanic) on the outside and "white" (Western) on the inside.
#* Related slang terms: [[banana]] - a person who is "yellow" (Asian) on the outside and "white" (Caucasian) on the inside, [[oreo]] - a person who is black (African American) on the outside and "white" (Caucasian) on the inside.  
# (''person'') a racial slur in [[w:New Zealand|New Zealand]] used to refer to [[w:Pacific islanders|Pacific islanders]].


